Rating: 4
I fall into the camp of best yellow cake ever. It has a lovely texture and a rich flavor. I have a few suggestions that I followed from other reviewers. First of all, I use organic ingredients. This is especially important for the buttermilk since most buttermilks have preservatives, stabilizers, and thickeners. I find those effect both the flavor and the performance of the buttermilk. Secondly, DON'T skimp on creaming the sugar and butter. I did all 12 tedious minutes of creaming, with a hand held mixer no less, but it gives the batter this amazing puffy texture. Lastly, IGNORE the cooking time. I baked cupcakes for 15 minutes and 9" cakes for 32 minutes.

