Well, I'm not sure what all the fuss is about this cake being dry. Quite the opposite here for me. I do subscribe to the idea that you should beat/cream your butter and sugar for an absurd amount of time to get a fluffier end product. Something my baking instructor was adamant about in my classes. I (unfortunately due to pantry limitations) had to use bread flour. I reduced it by 0.5C, and the results are fabulous. I substituted 1 tsp each of almond and vanilla extract instead of just vanilla. Personal preference. The only thought I have is that, as usual, the people who make ninety-million changes to the recipe, don't read thoroughly and carefully are probably blame for poor results. I believe this recipe is solid, the rations are all reasonable. My recommendation: read the recipe, lay out everything, read the recipe again, do the first step, read the recipe, do the second step, reread the recipe, and so on. You'll be pleasantly surprised. This cake is delicious when made correctly.

