Rating: 4
This recipe is stupendous. Moist and wonderful! I followed ingredients exactly but added a small box of instant pudding to the dry ingredients, also I always use caster sugar. I didn't really follow the preparation guidelines at all because I have a particular way I put a yellow cake batter together. Cream room temp butter and caster sugar until white and fluffy (this takes TIME, leave the mixer for 5 min or so). Add room temp eggs 1 at a time and mix well. Sift dry ingredients together. Combine buttermilk and vanilla. With the mixer speed set to slowest setting, add 1/4 dry, then 1/3 wet, and so on starting and ending with dry ingredients. Bake at 170C. Once the cake has cooled some, I recommend leveling off the top browned crust because it will be extra sugary and the cake underneath is perfect. If your cake didn't turn out moist you did something wrong. Don't feel bad, though, baking takes a lot of practice (believe me I've made many an unfortunate cornbread).

