Rating: 4
With the addition of 1/4tsp almond extract and 1 tsp princess cake and cookie emulsion this cake is incredible. I have tried three yellow layer recipes so far, and nothing compares to this one. Hands down, not even comparable. Soft, even rising. Easy to get out of the pan. Tender crumb, and most importantly MOIST. To those that thought it was dry, I have a few suggestions. -Make sure you use cake flour. Sift it before measuring. -Get an oven thermometer and USE IT. Once I got one, I realized why my cakes were not rising evenly, and getting dry! My oven runs about 15 degrees too hot, and we are at a high elevation. It is invaluable info to know. Now I follow the oven thermometer and not the displayed temp. -Follow all mixing instructions to the TEE. Time the minutes, actually do the small additions and scrape down after each one. One more thing I will mention. The grams in parenthesis by the US Measurement (cups etc) are, according to my digital scale, inaccurate. Every brand of flour, sugar etc weighs a little differently. I recommend weighing AND measuring in cups to determine if they are accurate for you before relying on the scale alone. I used explicitly cups etc for this recipe with great results. ENJOY! THis recipe is my new best friend. THANK YOU!

