Rating: 4
I agree with the positive reviews of this recipe. I made this cake for my sister's birthday and it has a very fine, soft, moist crumb. I did make a few minor adjustments to the recipe. 1) I put in an extra teaspoon of vanilla, and this gave it a really wonderful aroma; 2) I was in a bit of a rush, so I did NOT beat it for a full minute after each sugar addition; 3) I reserved about 1.5 cups of the final batter and added about 1/3 cup cocoa (I used Bellagio "Sipping Chocolate") and swirled in dollops of the batter to make a gorgeous marble cake. This yellow cake is quite pale, so the chocolate areas were striking. It does take an entire 45 minutes to bake, even if you used 9 inch cake pans instead of 8 inch pans, as I did. This is a really lovely cake. Fully cool it before icing, as it can be occasionally delicate.

